...useless check again. The knight threatens d4 once the queen moves away. White can't immediately move the d2 bishop to support the pawn, because I would capture the knight and double his pawns on the C file. However, with developing my knight, I left the b7 pawn undefended. I figured by this point I would capitalize on my advantage in development by gambitting the pawn and developing even more.
